    <section class="banner" id="faq">
        <div class="container">
            <div>
                <details>
                    <summary>1. What is The Bu Tone system?</summary>
                    <p><h5>The Bu Tone is a social networks for musicians, where they can share their pieces of music and participate in groups in order to build common products.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>2. Why I need to register and log-in in order to use The Bu Tone?</summary>
                    <p><h5>The Bu Tone is a system for musicians who wants to contribute to musical products, not a system meant to be used by their audience. If you are here, everyone expects from you to contribute and of course standing by it with your name and authority.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>3. How can I start a team to work with?</summary>
                    <p><h5>You should go to group page and start a new group. After that you can invite other people in your group and work with them on whatever you want.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>4. How can I upload a file of mine?</summary>
                    <p><h5>Go to my creations page and just click 'Add new'. That's it.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>5. How can I update a file, which I have already uploaded?</summary>
                    <p><h5>You do not need to bother about that. Just update again and we will keep the versions of you file adding timestamps to make it easy for you to get older version if needed.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>6. What is the crypto-signature I receive after an upload of a file?</summary>
                    <p><h5>This is an unique string of characters which holds the information about this particular upload, including the author and the time of uploading. You can save it in a secure place so you can claim authorship even if you lose the access to you The Bu Tone account.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>7. How I communicatite with other users?</summary>
                    <p><h5>You can message to all the people using the system in the public feed or message to the users in a particular group using group messages.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>8. Should I know all the people I work with?</summary>
                    <p><h5>No. You have to feel free and secure to work with complete strangers. Everything you upload is yours (not common) until you decide to change it's ownership.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>9. How can I change the ownership of my file?</summary>
                    <p><h5>Go to creations page. Click on creation and choose the new owner.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>10. Is there a limit of the storage I use?</summary>
                    <p><h5>Currently not but there will be some restrictions in the future.</h5></p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>11. What I have to do if I experience some trouble using the site or I see a bug in it?</summary>
                    <p><h5>Visit Contacts page and can drop a line to the site author.</h5></p>
                </details>
